---
// src/pages/blog/cyclist-decency-workshop.astro
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="AARBAA - Teaching Cyclists Basic Human Decency">
  <style slot="head">
    /* Page-specific color overrides */
    .text-b31942, .text-danger-aarbaa {
      color:rgb(150, 25, 11) !important; /* Workshop-specific red */
    }
    
    .bg-b31942, .bg-danger-aarbaa {
      background-color:rgb(124, 16, 4) !important; /* Workshop-specific red */
    }
    
    .border-b31942, .border-danger-aarbaa {
      border-color:rgb(113, 18, 7) !important; /* Workshop-specific red */
    }
    
    .btn-b31942, .btn-danger {
      background-color:rgb(95, 9, 0) !important; /* Workshop-specific red */
      border-color:rgb(87, 12, 3) !important; /* Workshop-specific red */
    }
    
    .btn-b31942:hover, .btn-danger:hover {
      background-color: #c0392b !important; /* Darker workshop-specific red */
      border-color: #c0392b !important; /* Darker workshop-specific red */
    }
    
    .text-0a3161, .text-primary-aarbaa {
      color: #2c3e50 !important; /* Workshop-specific blue */
    }
    
    .bg-0a3161, .bg-primary-aarbaa {
      background-color: #2c3e50 !important; /* Workshop-specific blue */
    }
    
    .border-0a3161, .border-primary-aarbaa {
      border-color: #2c3e50 !important; /* Workshop-specific blue */
    }
    
    .btn-0a3161, .btn-primary {
      background-color: #2c3e50 !important; /* Workshop-specific blue */
      border-color: #2c3e50 !important; /* Workshop-specific blue */
    }
    
    .btn-0a3161:hover, .btn-primary:hover {
      background-color: #1a2530 !important; /* Darker workshop-specific blue */
      border-color: #1a2530 !important; /* Darker workshop-specific blue */
    }
    
    /* Workshop-specific styles */
    .workshop-heading {
      font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif !important;
      color: #e74c3c !important;
      letter-spacing: 1px !important;
      border-bottom: 3px solid #e74c3c !important;
      padding-bottom: 10px !important;
      margin-bottom: 20px !important;
    }
    
    .workshop-blue-heading {
      font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif !important;
      color: #2c3e50 !important;
      letter-spacing: 1px !important;
      border-bottom: 3px solid #2c3e50 !important;
      padding-bottom: 10px !important;
      margin-bottom: 20px !important;
    }
  </style>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="text-center mt-5 pt-5" 
        style="
          padding-top: 100px !important;
          background-color: #2c3e50;
          background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)), url('/images/sternteacher.webp');
          background-size: cover !important; 
          background-position: center !important;
          background-repeat: no-repeat !important;
          min-height: 600px;
          color: white;
          margin-top: 76px;
          display: flex;
          align-items: center;
        ">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row justify-content-center">
                <div class="col-lg-10">
                  <div style="background-color: rgba(116, 16, 5, 0.9); display: inline-block; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);">
                        <h1 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; font-size: 3.5rem; letter-spacing: 2px; margin: 0; text-transform: uppercase;">CIVILIZATION 101: Teaching Cyclists Human Decency</h1>
                  </div>
                  <p class="lead mb-4">March 8, 2025 | The Day We Attempted to Civilize the Uncivil</p>
                </div>
          </div>
        </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Blog Content Section -->
  <section class="section-padding" style="background-color: #f8f8f8;">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row justify-content-center">
                <div class="col-lg-10">
                  <article class="bg-white p-5 shadow-lg" style="position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
                        <div style="position: absolute; top: -20px; right: -20px; width: 200px; height: 200px; background-color: #e74c3c; transform: rotate(45deg); z-index: 1;"></div>
                        
                        <div class="problem-text mb-5">
                          <p>ROAD ETIQUETTE: A CONCEPT SO FOREIGN</p>
                          <p>We might as well have been teaching quantum physics to kindergarteners.</p>
                        </div>

                        <p class="lead mb-4 text-danger" style="font-weight: bold;">Caution: This report contains shocking revelations about human behavior that may cause spontaneous face-palming.</p>

                        <h2 class="workshop-heading">THE GREAT DECENCY INTERVENTION</h2>

                        <div class="row g-4 mb-4">
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                                <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                                  <div class="card-body">
                                        <h4 class="text-danger-aarbaa">Workshop by the Numbers</h4>
                                        <ul class="list-unstyled">
                                          <li>üö≤ 200+ Attendees</li>
                                          <li>üö® 1 Massive Reality Check</li>
                                          <li>üìä 99% Resistance to Basic Logic</li>
                                          <li>üèÜ 0 Participation Trophies Awarded</li>
                                        </ul>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                          </div>
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                                <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                                  <div class="card-body">
                                        <h4 class="text-danger-aarbaa">Curriculum Highlights</h4>
                                        <ul class="list-unstyled">
                                          <li>üõë Red Lights: Not a Suggestion</li>
                                          <li>‚û°Ô∏è Single File: It's Not a Conga Line</li>
                                          <li>üöó Sharing Road: You're Not the Main Character</li>
                                          <li>üß† Basic Traffic Laws: They Exist</li>
                                        </ul>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>

                        <h2 class="workshop-heading">SHOCKING MOMENTS OF ENLIGHTENMENT</h2>

                        <p>Imagine our surprise when we discovered that explaining basic road courtesy was equivalent to teaching quantum mechanics to a goldfish. Our workshop wasn't just a meeting‚Äîit was an intervention of epic proportions.</p>

                        <blockquote class="bg-danger text-white p-4 my-4" style="font-style: italic; position: relative;">
                          <div style="position: absolute; top: -15px; left: -15px; width: 50px; height: 50px; background-color: white; transform: rotate(45deg);"></div>
                          <p>"We came, we lectured, we marginally improved humanity's collective road intelligence by 0.03%."</p>
                          <footer class="text-white-50">- Michael Chen, Chief Decency Instructor</footer>
                        </blockquote>

                        <div class="bg-light p-4 my-4" style="border-left: 5px solid #e74c3c;">
                          <h3 class="workshop-heading" style="border-bottom: none;">THE REFORMED: A RARE SPECIES</h3>
                          <p>Against all odds, a small contingent of cyclists actually attended and‚Äîwait for it‚Äîtook notes. These unicorns of the cycling world proved that evolution might still be possible.</p>
                          <ul>
                                <li>üïäÔ∏è 3 Cyclists showed genuine remorse</li>
                                <li>üßê 2 Actually asked intelligent questions</li>
                                <li>ü§Ø 1 Admitted to previously being "that guy"</li>
                          </ul>
                        </div>

                        <h2 class="workshop-heading">KEY LESSONS HAMMERED HOME</h2>

                        <ul class="list-unstyled">
                          <li class="mb-3">
                                <span class="badge bg-danger me-2">üö¶</span> 
                                Red Lights Are Not Optional Performance Art Installations
                          </li>
                          <li class="mb-3">
                                <span class="badge bg-danger me-2">üö≤</span> 
                                The Road Is Not Your Personal Training Ground
                          </li>
                          <li class="mb-3">
                                <span class="badge bg-danger me-2">üë•</span> 
                                Single File: It's Not a Cycling Parade
                          </li>
                          <li class="mb-3">
                                <span class="badge bg-danger me-2">ü§ù</span> 
                                Sharing Means Not Causing 17-Car Pileups
                          </li>
                        </ul>

                        <div class="text-center my-5">
                          <a href="#join" class="btn btn-danger btn-lg px-5 py-3" style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px; box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);">JOIN OUR CRUSADE OF COMMON SENSE</a>
                        </div>

                        <div class="alert alert-danger" role="alert" style="border-left: 5px solid #721c24;">
                          <strong>BREAKING:</strong> Local cyclists reportedly still confused by concept of "stopping" and "following rules". Research continues.
                        </div>

                        <p class="text-muted mt-4">Disclaimer: No lycra was harmed during the making of this workshop. (But many egos were.)</p>

                        <hr class="my-5" style="border-top: 2px dashed #e74c3c;">

                        <h2 class="workshop-blue-heading">WORKSHOP METHODOLOGY & MATERIALS</h2>

                        <div class="row">
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                            <img src="/images/sternteacher.webp" alt="Stern Teacher at Workshop" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-lg mb-4">
                          </div>
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                            <p>Our approach to the Cyclist Decency Workshop was carefully designed to penetrate even the most dense layers of cyclist entitlement. Using a combination of scientific data, dramatic reenactments, and what educators call "tough love" (or what we call "reality"), our team of road etiquette experts created a curriculum that left no excuse unaddressed.</p>
                            
                            <p>Workshop materials included our award-winning pamphlet "So You Think Traffic Laws Don't Apply To You: A Reality Check" and the interactive workbook "How Not To Be That Guy: 101 Ways To Stop Annoying Everyone On The Road."</p>
                          </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="card bg-light border-0 shadow-sm p-4 my-4">
                          <h3 class="workshop-blue-heading" style="border-bottom: 2px solid #2c3e50;">WORKSHOP SESSION BREAKDOWN</h3>
                          
                          <div class="row mt-3">
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                              <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                                <div class="card-header bg-danger text-white">
                                  <h5 class="card-title mb-0">Morning Session</h5>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                  <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">Fundamentals of Not Being Terrible</h6>
                                  <ul class="list-unstyled">
                                    <li>‚úì Basic Traffic Laws Review</li>
                                    <li>‚úì The Red Light Isn't a Suggestion</li>
                                    <li>‚úì Right of Way Isn't "Might Makes Right"</li>
                                  </ul>
                                </div>
                              </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                              <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                                <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                                  <h5 class="card-title mb-0">Afternoon Session</h5>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                  <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">Advanced Courtesy Concepts</h6>
                                  <ul class="list-unstyled">
                                    <li>‚úì Single File: A Revolutionary Concept</li>
                                    <li>‚úì Hand Signals: Not Just For Show</li>
                                    <li>‚úì The Revolutionary Art of Yielding</li>
                                  </ul>
                                </div>
                              </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-4">
                              <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                                <div class="card-header bg-dark text-white">
                                  <h5 class="card-title mb-0">Evening Session</h5>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                  <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">Rehabilitation & Commitment</h6>
                                  <ul class="list-unstyled">
                                    <li>‚úì Pledge Signing Ceremony</li>
                                    <li>‚úì Support Group Formation</li>
                                    <li>‚úì 12-Step Program Introduction</li>
                                  </ul>
                                </div>
                              </div>
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>

                        <h2 class="workshop-blue-heading">THE CYCLIST PLEDGE</h2>

                        <div class="card border-primary mb-4">
                          <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                            <h3 class="mb-0">Official AARBAA Cyclist Rehabilitation Pledge</h3>
                          </div>
                          <div class="card-body">
                            <p class="font-italic" style="font-style: italic;">As a reformed cyclist, I solemnly pledge to:</p>
                            <ol>
                              <li class="mb-2">Stop at all red lights, even when "nobody is looking"</li>
                              <li class="mb-2">Ride single file when vehicles need to pass</li>
                              <li class="mb-2">Use hand signals before turns and lane changes</li>
                              <li class="mb-2">Not pretend I'm competing in the Tour de France on public roads</li>
                              <li class="mb-2">Acknowledge that spandex does not grant me special road privileges</li>
                              <li class="mb-2">Remember that my carbon fiber frame is not made of vibranium and will not protect me from physics</li>
                              <li class="mb-2">Accept that coffee shops are not cyclist-only parking lots</li>
                              <li class="mb-2">Understand that car horns are not applause for my performance</li>
                            </ol>
                            <div class="text-center mt-3">
                              <div class="border-bottom border-dark d-inline-block" style="width: 200px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
                                <em>Cyclist Signature</em>
                              </div>
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert" style="border-left: 5px solid #0A3161;">
                          <strong>FUTURE WORKSHOPS:</strong> Due to surprising (if minimal) success, AARBAA will host quarterly cyclist decency workshops throughout 2025. Registration is now open for the June session, which will include the new module "How to Explain to Your Cycling Friends That They're the Problem."
                        </div>

                        <div class="row mt-5">
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h3 class="text-danger-aarbaa">Workshop Resources</h3>
                            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                              <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center">
                                <i class="fas fa-file-pdf me-3 text-danger"></i>
                                <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">Workshop Slides (PDF)</a>
                              </li>
                              <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center">
                                <i class="fas fa-book me-3 text-danger"></i>
                                <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">Decency Workbook Materials</a>
                              </li>
                              <li class="list-group-item d-flex align-items-center">
                                <i class="fas fa-certificate me-3 text-danger"></i>
                                <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">Pledge Certificate Template</a>
                              </li>
                            </ul>
                          </div>
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h3 class="text-danger-aarbaa">Host a Workshop</h3>
                            <p>Bring the Cyclist Decency Workshop to your community! Our trained facilitators can deliver this life-changing intervention in your town.</p>
                            <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request Information</a>
                            <p class="mt-2 small text-muted">*Warning: Results may vary. Some cyclists are beyond help.</p>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                  </article>
                </div>
          </div>
        </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
